com.facebook.buck.core.model.targetgraph.raw

Interface UnconfiguredTargetNode

  • All Superinterfaces:
    ComputeResult
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    ImmutableUnconfiguredTargetNode

    public interface UnconfiguredTargetNode
extends ComputeResult
    A target node with attributes kept in a map as oppose to in a structured object like in TargetNode.

    The attributes are coerced from raw data produced by build file parser, but they are not stored in a structured object as in TargetNode.

    The main purpose of having such nodes is to perform additional processing before storing them in a structured constructor arguments.
